Title: I'm the guy to Manage Your Airbnb (Downtown)
Description: "I'm a fine artist and I've been managing a pied a terre and Airbnb properties for numerous, satisfied clients. doing cleaning , greeting, maintenance and staging for the past 9 years. I've also worked at the Museum of the City of New York, talking with visitors, I've traveled a lot myself so I understand a lot of the basic needs that travelers have.", '', " I'm dependable, reliable and nice to be around. I'm a male in my mid fifties and I live in hamilton heights, I'm an early riser and I am currently looking to add 2 weekly gigs to my schedule. I charge $35 an hour with a four hour minimum, so I can do a turnaround in a small space, (studio or 1 BR) for 140, and a 5 story townhouse with 6 Bedrooms I can do for $600. Small jobs I do on my own and larger jobs I bring in freelancers to prep your 6 bedroom townhome within the standard 10 AM to 4 PM time frame between reservations.", '', "You take the bookings and email me the phone and address of your guests, I get in touch with them to find out when they'll be arriving at your place. I get to your space in advance of your guest's arrival clean, organize, restock supplies, change the linens. . ...do whatever needs to be done for your guests to have a great stay.", '', " Then I greet your guests, show them around the apartment, answer any questions they might have about the neighborhood and make sure they're happy. . ..", '', "I'll text you an invoice and you pay me by paypal. . ...done!", '', 'My service is called Nestprepper', '', 'google that for a link to my website and read my glowing reviews!', '', 'or email me for a link erik at nestprepper', '', 'I started doing this work in August of 2010. A friend of mine needed some help staging an apartment for sale and he brought me on board. We ended up working really well together and the apartment owner ender up hiring me to be her weekly housekeeper. I worked for this family for 3 years until their daughter graduated college and moved back home and they no longer needed me. . .The homeowner wrote me an excellent recommendation..', '', "It is my pleasure to recommend Erik Hanson as a housekeeper. Mr Hanson has worked for me since August of 2010, in the staging of our apartment for sale. We were so impressed with Mr. Hanson's work that we asked if he could be our regular housekeeper on a weekly basis.", '', "His thoroughness, trustworthiness, attention to detail, esthetic sensitivity and willingness to adapt to my and my families' schedule made him an asset to our household. In the aftermath of Hurricane Sandy we asked if he could help clean my mother in Law's apartment which had sustained severe damage as a result of the weather and a loss of power. Mr. Hanson came through with flying colors and helped our family through a very difficult time.", '', 'In addition, Mr. Hanson was sensitive to the many valuable artworks in our apartment and cared for them splendidly.', '', 'I quickly found work with a gentleman who was renting out his apartment on Airbnb. This lasted till January of 2014 when he decided to give up his apartment and move to London. . .he recently wrote this recommendation for me. . ..', '', '', '"Erik managed my space for me flawlessly for the past year. I emailed him the dates, names and contact info of the guests and Erik contacted them assuring them that he would be there upon their arrival, and he was, without fail there to great all of my guests after having spotlessly cleaned the space. My guests reported that he thoroughly oriented them to the apartment and neighborhood and assured them that he would come by to take of any problems, making my guests feel comfortable and secure. They often mentioned him by name in their reviews on Airbnb.', '', 'Erik was honest, direct and easy to work with. I knew that my property was in good hands. I trusted him implicitly and he never let me down. He was quick to go the extra mile when needed and even though he charged a bit more than some of the cleaners/managers/greeters that I had used previously what he saved me in headaches was easily worth the few extra dollars I paid him. Erik was calm, experienced, resourceful and an asset to my property. "', '', '', "I'm currently managing a pied a terre for a Connecticut banker and an upper east side co-op for airbnb and  2 bedroom in the east village on a regular basis. . .(i.e. once a week or more) over the summer, which is typically the busy season I was regularly working for 6 clients and all went well. . ..I'd like to add 2 weekly gigs to my schedule. I'd be happy to discuss your needs at your convenience so shoot me an email ", '', 'Thanks', '', '', 'Erik    '

Description: MPSTAR PROS. -  www.mpstarpros.com', '+Licensed and Insured!', '', '"The objective of cleaning is not just to clean, but to feel happiness living within that environment."', '', 'AirBnB Cleaning/ Turnover now available!', '', 'Deep cleaning at MPStar Pros differs from our maintenance cleanings in several key ways. Your deep cleaning visit is more like spring cleaning or perhaps Ã¢â‚¬Å“catch-upÃ¢â‚¬Â cleaning. Even if you keep a straight and organized home, dirt, dust, residue, can accumulate, and if it has been there for long it takes a lot more effort to remove. Before we can begin regularly scheduled cleaning of a home, there are a variety of tasks that require extra time and effort. There is a big difference between Ã¢â‚¬Å“oldÃ¢â‚¬Â dirt and Ã¢â‚¬Å“newÃ¢â‚¬Â dirt. If we donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t get rid of the old dirt first, no matter how hard we try, simply removing new dirt isnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t going to to make your home sparkling clean. It is not uncommon for us to spend from two to three times as long on a deep cleaning than it takes on regular, repeat maintenance visits.', '', 'Hand washing baseboards and woodwork throughout your home is a big reason that deep cleaning visits can take more time. We also spend additional time in your kitchen in bathrooms detail cleaning. Think of it like a spa treatment for your home.', '', 'At MPStar Pros we believe in fair and flexible pricing for all of our services. We know that a deep cleaning can be a big investment in your home. We promise we will never exceed your quoted price without prior verbal or written approval. The quote you receive is a do not exceed price. This price is for a set amount of labor hours. In most cases this will be more than enough time to give your home a very thorough and complete cleaning. However. Some homes need more attention the first visit. If that is the case, we can work out a plan to fit your needs or budget. We can clean it all now if you approve extra time. We can catch it up on future visits. ', '', 'Testimonial:', "To label what Nancy does as 'organizing' is like comparing Desmond Tutu to a garden variety preacher: she elevates seemingly ordinary work to a high art. Title: Housekeeper / Meal prep 30$ per hour! 3hrs per day! (Upper East Side)
Description: Hello!', 'We are a family of 5 living in the upper east side. We are looking for a housekeeper from 9am-12pm from monday to thursday. The role of the person would be to spend 1.5-2 hours tidying up the house (make the beds, clean up breakfast dishes, tidy childrens rooms etc), and 1-2 hours preparing dinner for that night for the family of 5. Note that we have a regular housekeeper who does a "deep clean" of the house every friday, which we intend to keep. So this role is in supplement to that! From time to time we may ask the person to get the required groceries for dinner that night, etc.', 'We are willing to pay $30 per hour. We are relatively simple people, who are not looking for anything too extravagant. But rather a little extra help as our 3 kids keep us very busy! Some experience in food prep is required. ', '', '', '', 'housekeeper, maid, chef, cook, cleaning services    '
